content:
The Analytics tab provides a modern and cohesive experience for organizing all your analytics content in one place. You can access all your reports and dashboards in a single location, making it easier for you to manage and analyze your data.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials, Group, Enterprise, Professional, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

To access the Analytics tab:
Enhanced Folder Sharing is required.
Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards are also required.

Use the search bar for keyword searches and Browse to locate specific reports and dashboards. The cards in For You organize your reports and dashboards and help you find what you’re looking for quickly. Go to My Analytics to access content from a chronological listing and Favorites. Use Collections to curate and organize analytics across different folders, and share them with other users.

Find the last report or dashboard that you worked with or see what’s available on the Analytics tab. Browse enables you to quickly locate the items you’re looking for by filtering through different categories.

Favorite your reports and dashboards for quick access, such as My Analytics, and throughout the Analytics tab.

Collections enable you to curate and organize your analytics in a customized way. By creating a collection, you have a personalized set of analytics that’s relevant to your projects or interests.

Create reports and dashboards right from the Analytics tab. Rather than opening multiple tabs, you can stay in one app and create the analytics you want.

Use enhanced folder sharing to share a report or dashboard folder with users, groups, roles, or territories.
title: Managing Salesforce Analytics
